<Layout
	title="About Shed Flips"
	description="Lonnie and Candice flip garage-sale and estate-sale finds online — eBay, Mercari, Etsy, Poshmark, wherever they land best."
	pubDate={new Date('April 29 2026')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>Shed Flips</strong> is Lonnie and Candice — a husband-and-wife team running a small
		reselling operation out of a shed in South Louisiana. We source items at garage sales, estate
		sales, auctions, and thrift stores, then flip them online (eBay, Mercari, Etsy, Poshmark,
		wherever the item lands best). The shed is where it all happens: the staging, the photography,
		the listing, the packing.
	</p>

	<p>
		This site is the written companion to <em>four</em> YouTube channels we're a part of:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong><a href="/shed-flips">Shed Flips</a></strong> — the flagship channel. Long-form sourcing days, sold-stats wrap-ups, and strategy talk.</li>
		<li><strong><a href="/im-gonna-pack-it">I'm Gonna Pack It</a></strong> — packing-day companion channel. The orders going out, the packing tricks, the boxes we pick.</li>
		<li><strong><a href="/garage-flips">Garage Flips</a></strong> — quick-cut shorts from the garage-sale circuit. Newer channel, more frequent drops.</li>
		<li><strong><a href="/podcast">The Lonnie & Ryan Podcast</a></strong> — weekly podcast Lonnie does with his friend Ryan. Reseller talk, guests, longer-form conversation.</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Each post here is a written companion to one specific video. The video is always embedded at the
		top, so you can watch, read, or both. The post itself adds whatever the video doesn't already
		say — exact prices, the lessons we'd take into the next sale, timestamps that jump you straight
		to the moment you came for.
	</p>

	<h2>What you'll find here</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>Hauls from real days at real sales — what we paid, what we picked, what we passed on</li>
		<li>Sold-stats wrap-ups — what moved on which platform and for how much</li>
		<li>Pack-day write-ups — the orders, the box choices, the occasional FiestaWare apology</li>
		<li>Strategy notes from years of doing this — pricing, photos, listing copy, fees</li>
		<li>Lessons learned the hard way — shipping cost surprises, condition mistakes, all of it</li>
		<li>Episode notes for the podcast — timestamped highlights of conversations worth jumping to</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Stay in touch</h2>

	<p>
		Pick a channel from the top of the page to see what's been on each one. If you'd rather follow
		new posts as they land, the <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> collects everything across all four
		channels in one place.
	</p>
</Layout>
